title: Excellent workmanship and beautiful and heavy clock; dials may touch due to shipment - 4.5 stars
text:
I dropped my previous very cheap wall clock and broke it when I was changing time twelve days ago when we sprung ahead for Daylight Savings Time. Since I wanted something more substantial and different and since I love craft items, I settled on this clock.

I decided to use a beautiful photo of one of my three cats. I attached the photo so that you can see the one that was used and how the clock came out. I picked the mahogany wood since there was no super light wood available. The clock itself came out great. The numbers on the clock are perfect. The reproduced photo is almost perfect. What I mean by that is that it is more muted than the actual photograph but that is to be expected. There is a long channel on the back of the clock that starts with a circle to slip onto a screw head and then the clock can be slid to the left along the channel to adhere to the wall. This works perfectly as long as the head on the screw (not included) is small.

Obviously, this clock is too big and too dark where I put it, but it is going to stay there as my other clock's replacement. It would look best in an area by itself or with more room away from my other framed picture. It would also look better with very light wood like the frame color of the canvas below it (see photos of the clock on the wall).

The only negative is that the dials arrived squished against each other. I had to pull the second and minute hands apart a little bit and tighten the knob on front. The AA battery (not included) goes in the back. The mechanism in back did turn out of kilter when setting the clock, so I had to be careful to keep that in place as well. That is also to be expected based on other clocks I have with this type mechanism.

As a side note, my cat's reaction to this clock is extremely surprising. About two hours after putting this up, my cat looked at his photo on the clock. This is more than interesting because cats are not self-aware. I had to take a photo of this, which I attached here. He approves but he looks puzzled why his likeness is up there on the wall.

In summary, I love the quality of this timepiece and the results. The time mechanism itself, however, is problematic during shipping and can get out of alignment. The photo will also be more subdued than the original. The price is perfect for this handmade gem. The turnaround time from order placement to fulfillment and receipt is fabulous--in total it took 12 calendar days. I placed my order on March 7 and received my treasure today on March 19, 2020. I love it and wish I had a better place to put it that would highlight its workmanship.

title: Attention to detail- quality made.. a few caveats to think of..
text:
Straightforward, embroidery floss bracelet with attention to detail and quality finish. Nothing bulky- it is tightly bound on x2 thinner silk strands of floss.. knotted ends keep from fraying or fly away ends and evenly placed knots fall on each side to hold tiny pendant in place, upright and centered.

Slip knot clasp offers ability to put on/adjust using one hand which is ideal! One size will fit adult or child by simple tightening or loosening of pull strings. Designed unisex the center heart shape bead may not be perceived by all as such! Tbh, ours was gifted to 19yr old boy from 3yr bff nephew- and he loves to wear 24/7 because of meaning to him. But something to keep in mind for recipient.

The handmade feature elevates the effort/thoughtfulness of any gift..
I wish that was made known to the recipient when gifting. Including that fact on the tag or insert card- it's a great feature to let it be known. Note to seller! For price point being higher.. I feel using a sterling silver metal center bead- one that would not tarnish or fade would be best. A small increase in cost to make but would justify price being more acceptable- well, creating longevity for wearing!

Overall, very nicely crafted bracelet- sold at higher price point than most- only reason for 4 star. Hoping info helps decision- stay safe everyone!

title: Best as a gift- high end and personalized..
text:
Very fun and aesthetically bright colored salts layered to look enticing.. the fun names and “flavors” have ability to give these a personal fit for a number of gift scenarios: bday, bridal, new mama, wedding destination, anniversary, thx you, retirement, etc.. Anytime a bougie bubble bath fits the bill..!!

These leave soft skin nothing irritating which is a plus for sensitive skin. Although scent is present while opening pouch- it dissipates when salts are placed in water.. leaving a saltwater aroma! Very eye catching with presentation window.. but, in use they don't have a big “wow” factor- I realize, to some that's appealing. But so all are aware- no fizz, color swirling, bubbles, etc. Prob. safe to assume these have healing properties from the salts- but, no product ingredient listing or info. on item to back this up.

I love the idea of homemade and supporting “mom+pop” shop goods.. truly I do!! Only, I find this pricier then most for an outcome of soft bathwater. This is definitely gift worthy and that aspect is not disappointing and it's best feature.. to give a personalized spoiler- I find it hard to justify $20 for a pound of bath salts in any color/flavor.. in a throwaway pouch.

Note: scrub/rinse bathtub after use! After x2-3 consecutive uses… salt left slippery residue in porcelain tub. To avoid film or slip hazard- use regular bathroom cleaner to remove. Hoping info can help your decision- stay safe everyone!

I won't go into detail on how these are made, but the process shines through in the finished product. I ordered this Memento Mori coin necklace and due to postal errors, it was returned to sender after making it all the way to my mailbox.  I contacted the seller and they were immediately responsive and offered to ship the item again at no charge.  This sort of customer service is hard to come by, and it's nice to see that the coins aren't the only thing old fashioned.  I truly love the necklace.  It is somewhat heavy (.999 fine silver), and the weight serves as a gentle reminder that it is there.  The chain is pretty basic and a nice bonus, but I wasn't ordering it for the chain.  Overall, if you're on the fence about paying a little more for a conversation starting necklace, just buy this one.  After you get it, you'll be looking to see what else they have for sale as I am!

title: Really nice in person and has already worked to stop the UPS guy with the doorbell
text:
I actually love the sign we received. It's big enough to be easily read and the customization of the dog images is terrific. I wanted a Swiss Mountain Dog and a Rhodesian Ridgeback and they look great - no doubt what breeds the images are representing. There's a grooved hanger attached on the back for use with a nail, but I added a wire to it and attached it to our actual doorbell instead.

Normally, I would never include mail drama in my overall review of any product from Amazon, but the sign is from an independent party and that's a bit different. It was exactly 22 days from order to receipt and I find that excessive and puzzling. This is a basic template design that requires very little extra work for the personalization so three weeks is way too long to wait.

Nonetheless, the sign will hopefully save me from buying yet another doorknob because my Plott Hound has lost his mind over the doorbell. And it's definitely earned some smiles from my husband and even our UPS man this morning - he did not ring the bell!

text:

However, it is one of the messiest balms I have ever used and the container that this balm comes in should be changed out because it is not suited for these types of things. This balm comes in a shallow tin that is not air-tight, at all, and therefore leaks with the slightest shake or turn of the container. They do package the balm in plastic when it is sent out, so thank goodness for that because you could see oil all in the bag when it arrived. I thought it might have just been from shipping but it continued to leak and everything even after being opened because the balm itself never fully solidifies but stays in this middle of half liquid, half mush state. I finally had to put it into a glass container that I had in order for it to stop leaking and making a mess all over everything.
While the product is pretty good, the packaging makes it to where I do not want to use this stuff again because the mess isn't worth it. Especially when I can get similar products, with better packaging that does a better job for a better price.

I still really like the scent though, and it wouldn't hurt for it to be tripled scented than what it is now.
The pumpkin spice scent is okay. It isn't horrible but it isn't that great either. It doesn't have a lot of fragrance and doesn't last but only a few hours if that.
Overall these were some of the worst wax cubes that I have bought and I DO NOT recommend these at all. If they changed the scents and added more scents to these, then maybe that would make these better but as they are right now, I will NEVER buy these again. I would much rather spend the money and get Scenty wax melts.

title: Shattered within seconds of receiving.
text:
First it was very tiny, which at least the measurement was in the description. Second, you need to tie your own slip knots for the cord, which they did include a print out of how to do that yourself, although it looked like the printer was running out of ink because I couldn't make out the words for the direction's because it was so light.
But what really sucked is all I did was slip it over my head and I heard a small thump sound and I looked down to see the cat pendant on the carpet broken. The only way I can see that happening is if there were fractures in the carved stone that were barely holding together that by the time of me just moving the cord over my head that it just broke and fell off the loop.

Complete waste of money and way too much money at that. I was excited about finding this online and it arriving but deeply disappointed in the outcome.

title: Nice polish ...
text: I'm not very girly when it comes to things like makeup and nails ... rather a tomboy.  So when I say this polish is nice, believe me ... it's great!  It went on evenly (even though it does take a bit longer to dry than regular polish ... so I messed a few nails up but with a top coat, doesn't look that bad!) although it does feel bumpy due to the glitter ... the top coat smoothed it out.  Very shiny and after a day of typing (I use the tops of my fingers), haven't had a chip yet!  I'm rather impressed ... not sure about the color and me (it changes to a darker pink and somewhat of a purple depending on the light in the room) but it's not bad ... I'm going to try a more neutral color, too ... I do like the sparkle and my grandson noticed the glittering right off the bat!  I think you get what you pay for ... the more expensive polishes seem to last longer and for me (with the top coat), hasn't chipped or peeled yet!  Yeah!  I'll definitely purchase more!

title: Maybe overpriced but worth it!!
text: This is a beautiful pendant by Missia. The packaging is lovely - a faux leather box which holds a wooden (walnut), mirrored heart. Inside the heart is a lovely, very feminine silver pendant. A single, large moissanite stone is set inside a setting that reminds me of lopsided, colliding hearts. It dangles from a thin, sterling silver chain. The center stone does have some sparkle without looking like cheap costume jewelry. Inside is a packet that includes a polishing cloth, authenticity card and small note. Some may think this necklace is overpriced, but the packaging definitely accounts for some of the cost. I'd recommend it.

title: The perfect gift to give - A night of pampering or relaxing!!

The small box is filled with several heavenly lavender smelling items: (1) a 4.5 oz of body butter, (2) a 3.5 oz bar of soap, (3) a bath bomb and (4) a 3oz cylinder of bath salts. The 5th item is a drawstring bag which can hold the soap or really any item(s) that you'd like.  Overall, this is a great kit meant for pampering and relaxing.  Perfect for yourself or someone else. I'd recommend it.

The pearls themselves are a nice size (6-7mm/7-8 mm) - both the ones on the posts and that dangle at the end. I definitely would recommend.

title: Smells like you are on a Caribbean vacation!
text: What is better than sitting on the beach sipping a cool, refreshing mixed drink? What could make it better - incorporating a nice, hot bath while sipping that drink! So, what is the closest thing you can do if you can't go on said vacation? Well, take a bath in something that smells fruity and fun! The “You Clean” bath salts bring both of these elements (a drink and a bath) together. This Fizzy Foaming Bath Salt smells faintly of “Sex on the Beach.” It smells absolutely delicious and isn't overwhelming at all! This product comes in a 17oz resealable bag, filled with a dusty/fine/colorful powder in bold/bright/colorful colors:  hot pink, yellow and orange. The salts are a combination of Epsom and Mediterranean Sea salt, which is very soothing and relaxing. It is sulfate, paragon, gluten and phthalate free. Overall, this is decent product that will make a nice gift for yourself or someone else. 4 stars.

title: Two-toned delight!

I have sensitive skin and didn't notice any irritation or redness. While the packaging is simple, I did like that it included a “thank you” label on the box. These earrings are very classy and can be worn everyday. Overall, these are some cute earrings for under $16.

title: Nice scalp oil!
text: I love how this scalp oil (by Pollination) because it can even be applied when I have braids. The bottle, which has an applicator, can be used to apply a small amount easily. This oil has a nice bland scent, nothing too loud or annoying. Although this is a quality oil, it isn't overly greasy/oily but produces a nice shine. It moisturizes, nourishes and softens wet or dry hair. There are a combination of several ingredients that do this: they include dragon's blood resin, ginger, neem, olive and castor oil, rosemary and vitamin E - all of which are believed to stimulate hair growth. There are no additives - sulfates, paragons, mineral oils, silicones or dyes. And finally, the 2oz container runs about $39 on Amazon, and while this is a bit pricey, that is ok if it does all it is supposed to.

title: Only time will tell if it grows my hair, but it feels healthy!
text: This Pollynation hair stimulator is a great product that promotes healthy hair. It is a butter but has the consistency of a light grease. It doesn't make your hair look heavy or oily, but provides a nice sheen. It is perfect for my natural, coarse hair. It isn't overly greasy and feels great on the scalp. I simply part my hair and add a small amount on my fingertips before applying.  The scent is pleasant enough, nothing too bold or overwhelming. While I have not used it long enough to see if it grows my hair, I can tell you that it leaves my hair moisturized and soft. It contains olive and coconut oil, beeswax, shea butter and vitamin E. No bad additives included - like silicone, paragons, sulfate, phthalates or formaldehyde. You can apply to wet or dry hair. I can also add a little to the palm of my hand and work though my hair (wet or dry), then style as usual. Finally, a 2oz container of this product, is a bit pricey (around $33 dollars on Amazon) but might be worth it if it works.

title: Fashionable and is believed to have healing powers!

You can stack this bracelet, if you have more than one. This bracelet is unisex - so will look great on both men and women. It will also match any and everything - from jeans to a dress. I haven't decided if that is true or not, but I know it looks pretty. Overall, I give this bracelet 5 stars.

title: A lovely leather tote!
text: This tote by Pascado is nice. It is rugged and well made. There are shoulder straps (two sizes). The leather is an orangey-brown, which will match most outfits. The inside of the bag is lined. There are two front pockets (magnetic closures) and a rear zippered one. There are also two side pockets which are useful if you want to slip an umbrella inside. The size of the tote is decent and can hold a variety of items (essentials and a small electronic). *The electronics I would consider are a small iPad mini or Kindle. Either would fit fine. The front or side pockets can hold a small cell phone or keys. I have a OnePlus cell phone that fits fine. And finally, I love that this company always encloses a nice “thank you letter,” which is a great touch! I'd recommend this tote.

title: Disappointed. Not a complete kit.
text: When I selected this DIY activity, I expected a little more. I thought I would get 4 complete art kits for a sip and paint event. I plan to use them for my upcoming birthday. I plan to have 3 friends over, give them a pre-printed canvas (this one is cute and says “Queen”) and let them be creative while sipping some wine and munching on appetizers. So, when I received this set, I was surprised to see (especially considering the price) that this only came with the canvases, no paints or brushes? The canvas is cute, but I mean for $60 (on Amazon), they could have provided 3 cheap brushes and 6 paints with each canvas! So, here is my biggest complaint: if this is a paint and sip kit, why not provide everyone with a complete kit, which would include the brushes and paints? That would make more sense. For me, ordering this kind of kit is for convenience. Who has time to run out and try to find the accompanying materials? That means more expense and more time spent running around. In conclusion, I am disappointed….and can only give this 3 stars.

title: Strong smell but dies down quickly!
text: The V.I.P. Rosemary & Shea butter hair and body butter is nice. I love the container. It is wooden. The product contains Jamaican castor oil, rosemary, lavender oil, and raw shea butter. These ingredients are moisturizing, conditioning, and hydrating. The smell (floral and herbs) can be initially overwhelming but quickly dies down. I use it on my body, especially my feet (great on my heels) once I get out of the shower. I haven't tried it on my hair, but definitely can see the benefit(s). It initially looks greasy but dissipates quickly. I have dry or sensitive skin and have had absolutely no problem with rashes or irritation. The texture is thick, like most shea products, and all you have to do is rub it in your hands before rubbing it on your body. Overall, I like this product. 4 stars.

title: WHY I edited from ONE star to FOUR stars
text:
EDIT: Vendor DID make name larger. While I wish it were even larger, GARDEN is still much larger, it now looks acceptable in size and I will be giving to the family tomorrow.

The size of the name was my biggest issue and now you can see the name clearly from more than just a few feet away.

I was assured this sign is rust proof and the scratches, marks are meant to be there to look more rustic.
If it rusts, I will adjust review, but I am taking vendor's word for that.

BOTTOMLINE:
IF you are looking for a cute, casual personalized tin sign, MY ONE SUGGESTION is to ASK VENDOR to make name larger, even if you have to pay more. MAKES ALL THE DIFFERENCE!
______________________________________________________________________

FIRST, I wasn't expecting a high end sign. A tin sign was fine. And that part is as I figured it would be.

HOWEVER, I got the BIGGEST of the options because I wanted it to stand out. A memorial sign for one of the gardens a friend had done because of Covid there was no service and this was my way of honoring him.

YOU HAVE NO IDEA how small the name really looks, even the images put up doesn't really bring it home til you see it. In fact, before I even ordered, I asked if the name could be in CAPS to make it bigger and at that time had no idea just how SMALL it would look. I said I wanted the sign whether or not could be done in caps.

FIRST, it took longer to get here than I was told, but I will add that under vendor comments.

SECOND, I got it today and GARDEN is big and the letters in the name are about....ONE THIRD the size, maybe even less, of the letters in GARDEN! It looks RIDICULOUS.

THIRD, the lettering is SCRATCHED, badly. It's not part of a distressed look or to go with the faux wood grain on the tin sign, it's SCRATCHED. Which means it can RUST when it rains. And there are LOTS of scratches. I have added a zoomed in close up. I was told it was meant to be this way, but you can FEEL the scratches and it makes the TINY lettering on the name look even worse.

FOUR, YES, came in a cardboard box, but not even a light layer of saran wrap around to keep from bumps or bruises, much less any bubble wrap.

I have decided NOT to give to family because I'm embarrassed by it. And embarrassed no one will even be able to READ the name even on the BIGGEST option of sign from the fence it will go on. You can see GARDEN from yards away, but the SMALL lower case name, you can't be more than feet away to notice and even then it's SO DWARFED by the word GARDEN.

BUT BEWARE....just getting the bigger sign doesn't mean you will see the name unless you are pretty close up.
I HAVE NO IDEA who thought making the NAME in a sign you obviously want personalized with that person's name, spending the money and time waiting for it, SOOOOO SMALL.

I chose the varnished finish option and a wonderful shellac odor escapes when you open the package. It is a rewarding experience to see total strangers lounging on a patio sipping cappuccino and flipping through your free books.
